r therefore from whence thou art fallen, and repent, and do the first works; or else I will come unto thee quickly, and will remove thy candlestick out of his place, except thou repent.","year":96},{"id":"rec24FlgptIg5HB3Y","ref":"Rev.2.6","text":"But this thou hast, that thou hatest the deeds of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.","year":96},{"id":"recWztsyqqTN7JrRz","ref":"Rev.2.7","text":"He that hath an ear, let him hear what the Spirit saith unto the churches; To him that overcometh will I give to eat of the tree of life, which is in the midst of the paradise of God.","year":96},{"id":"recmCDTfeollUadSq","ref":"Rev.2.8","text":"And unto the angel of the church in Smyrna write; These things saith the first and the last, which was dead, and is alive;","year":96}]}
